      • matches

        public boolean matches(WiFi other)
        Matches the wifi context of the given network against this network context. It is a match if WiFi is connected and has the same SSID for both contexts. It is also a match, if both contexts have connected WiFi and one (or both) have "%" configured as their WiFi SSID.
        Specified by:
        matches in class VContextType<WiFi>
        Parameters:
        other - The network context to match WiFi state against.
        Returns:
        True, if both contexts match. False, if not
